        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-09T15:06:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am fine with both of those.\noptions are not expected to change often (certainly not every commit). Additionally, the philosophy of Gold assumes that there is exactly one data point per trace per commit. I don\u0027t think I want to support retrying.",
